Babacan Says ’Bitter’ Turkish Measures Possible, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-05-16T05:20:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/babacan-says-bitter-turkish-measures-possible-hurriyet-says.html
Turkey  may introduce "bitter
measures" to preserve economic stability in the face of global
risks, Hurriyet newspaper reported, citing Deputy Prime Minister
 Ali Babacan .  Authorities have to be "very, very careful" in managing the
economy in the face of large external risks, Babacan said in
Kizilcahamam near Ankara, the newspaper reported.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
